│ source always fits into the destination type, which is not guaranteed by the  │
│ observed LVI results and leads to UB in the provided case.                    │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ The incorrect addition of nuw/nsw flags on trunc in CVP is the root cause. By │
│ disabling the processTrunc deduction of no-wrap flags, we prevent             │
│ introduction of poison semantics and restore correctness. This avoids the     │
│ Alive2 failure and ensures CVP remains conservative when dealing with trunc   │
│ casts, which are particularly sensitive to poison semantics. If we later want │
│ to reintroduce such deductions, they must be backed by stronger global        │
│ guarantees (e.g., proven range constraints invariant across all paths) and    │
│ careful handling of poison/undef considerations.                              │
